#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1550
msgid "How do Flexy Breadcrumbs work?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1554
msgid ""
"Flexy Breadcrumbs generates a contextual path for posts, pages, taxonomies and archives. Add the function in your theme where the "
"breadcrumb trail should appear."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1556
msgid ""
"The $pre and $after arguments let you wrap the output with your own markup. If you leave them empty, Flexy SEO prints only the "
"breadcrumb markup."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1557 admin/pageshandler.class.php:1798
msgid "Options:"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1559
msgid "Use the Breadcrumbs page to define a structure for every entity: posts, pages, taxonomies, archives and custom post types."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1560
msgid "With flexible breadcrumbs you can mix dynamic replacements, custom text and custom links in the same path:"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1563
msgid ">>"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1563
msgid "separates each breadcrumb item."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1566 admin/pageshandler.class.php:1569
msgid "Text"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1566
msgid "uses the value only as visible breadcrumb text."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1569
msgid "uses the value only as breadcrumb URL."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1572
msgid "/custom/link/"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1572
msgid "adds a custom link structure."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1575
msgid "replaces the matching WordPress query variable. If it is not available, it is discarded."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1578
msgid "replaces a meta value from the current queried object. If it is empty, it is discarded."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1581
msgid "prints the configured home breadcrumb item."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1585
msgid "prints the taxonomy or category path for the current object. Hierarchical terms generate multiple breadcrumb items."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1589
msgid "works like the taxonomy/category replacements, but keeps the taxonomy prefix in each term link."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1592
msgid "Replace the parent post of the current queried object."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1595
msgid "Replace the post type of the current queried object."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1598
msgid "Replace the title and link of the current queried object."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1602
#, php-format
msgid "Example: %%home%% >> (/%%meta_var%%-%%custom_var%%/)%%category%% >> %%queried_object%%"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1606
msgid "Use the <em>wpfs_breadcrumb_style</em> filter to change the default breadcrumb CSS."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1607
msgid ""
"Use the <em>wpfs_breadcrumb_replacements</em> filter to add or override breadcrumb replacements. The return format must be "
"<strong>array(array('text' =>, 'url' => ))</strong>."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1615
msgid "How does Flexy SEO generate metadata?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1619
msgid ""
"Flexy SEO starts from the template configured for the current context, applies WordPress filters, replaces dynamic tokens and then "
"normalizes the final title, description, keywords, social metadata and schema output."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1620
msgid ""
"This means one template can adapt to posts, taxonomies, archives, search pages and custom post types without duplicating manual SEO "
"rules."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1622
#, php-format
msgid "See the complete replacer list <a href=\"%s\">here</a>."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1629
msgid "What are replacers and when should I use them?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1633
#, php-format
msgid ""
"Replacers are dynamic tokens such as %%title%%, %%description%%, %%sitename%%, %%sep%% and %%meta_price%%. They are replaced with the "
"value available in the current page context."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1634
msgid ""
"Use them when a rule should work across many pages. For example, a product post type can use one title template while each product "
"still receives its own title, category, excerpt and custom fields."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1642
msgid "How does autosave work in the SEO panel?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1646
msgid ""
"The SEO settings page saves changes automatically after you edit a field. A status badge and toast notification show whether changes "
"are pending, saving, saved or blocked by a connection error."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1647
msgid "If you leave the page while a change is still pending, the browser warns you before closing so you do not lose unsaved settings."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1654
msgid "What should I configure first?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1658
msgid ""
"Start with General settings, then configure the Home page, Post types and Taxonomies. After that, review Social and Schema.org "
"settings so shared links and structured data are consistent with your brand."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1660
msgid "Set the title separator and whether the site name should be appended automatically."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1661
msgid "Create one strong title and description template for each important post type."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1662
msgid "Add a default wide and small image for pages that do not have a usable featured image."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1663
msgid "Enable Schema.org and fill organization data if the site represents a business, agency or brand."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1671
msgid "How are title and meta description fallbacks handled?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1675
msgid ""
"If a configured template produces an empty value, Flexy SEO builds a fallback from the current context: post excerpt or content, term "
"description, author description, search query or site description."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1676
msgid ""
"The final text is cleaned before output: unresolved tokens, shortcodes, HTML tags and excessive spaces are removed so search engines "
"receive a readable value."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1683
msgid "How do Open Graph and Twitter Card settings affect sharing?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1687
msgid ""
"Open Graph controls how links appear on Facebook, LinkedIn and other platforms that read og:* tags. Twitter Card controls twitter:* "
"tags and lets you choose standard or large image cards."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1688
msgid ""
"Flexy SEO reuses the generated SEO title, description, canonical URL and best available image, so social previews stay aligned with "
"the page metadata."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1695
msgid "Which Schema.org type should I choose?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1699
msgid ""
"Use WebPage for static pages, Article or BlogPosting for editorial posts, CollectionPage for archives and listing pages, "
"SearchResultsPage for search pages and RealEstateListing for property listing contexts."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1700
msgid ""
"The selected graph type is still dynamic: Flexy SEO fills URL, title, description, language, breadcrumb, dates, author and image data "
"from the current WordPress object when available."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1707
msgid "When should I clear the Flexy SEO cache?"
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1711
msgid ""
"Clear the cache after major template changes, taxonomy restructures, permalink changes or when you suspect old generated data is still "
"being reused."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1712
msgid ""
"For normal edits in the SEO panel, autosave updates the stored settings immediately and the frontend generator will use the new rules "
"on subsequent requests."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1734
msgid "Flexy SEO cache cleared."
msgstr ""

#: admin/pageshandler.class.php:1740
msgid "Permalink and sitemap rewrite rules refreshed."
msgstr ""

